info.name: 📌 Hugging Face API
info.description:
### Prerequisites

- Postman
- Hugging Face Account: [https://huggingface.co/](https://huggingface.co/)
    

### Usage

1. Create a fork
2. Update collection variables
3. Send requests (on 503 due to model loading, retry)
    

### Documentation

- API: [https://huggingface.co/docs/api-inference/index](https://huggingface.co/docs/api-inference/index)
- Models: [https://huggingface.co/models](https://huggingface.co/models)
    

### About Hugging Face

The AI community building the future.

request.description:
**Image classification** models classify images into one or more categories.

Available categories vary by model. For example, a model may specialize in estimating the age range of a person based on a picture of their face.

Image can be a link or base64

See available [Image Classification models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=image-classification&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [nateraw/vit-age-classifier](https://huggingface.co/nateraw/vit-age-classifier) | Predicts age range based on image of a person's face |
| [google/vit-base-patch16-224](https://huggingface.co/google/vit-base-patch16-224) | Identifies main object in image |
| [Nahrawy/AIorNot](https://huggingface.co/Nahrawy/AIorNot) | Classifies liklihood of an image being "real" or "ai" generated |
| [jayanta/google-vit-base-patch16-224-face](https://huggingface.co/jayanta/google-vit-base-patch16-224-face) | detects emotions from facial expressions in an image (happy, neutral, disgust, sad) |
| [skyau/dog-breed-classifier-vit](https://huggingface.co/skyau/dog-breed-classifier-vit) | Classifies dog breed by image |

item.description:
Images can be sent as

- URLs
    
- base64
    
- binary data
    

In the case of binary data, paste the following into a Postman request URL to create the basic request. Then in the Body of the request, use the filepicker helper.

```
curl --request POST \
  --url https://api-inference.huggingface.co/models/:model \
  --header 'Content-Type: image/jpg' \
  --data-binary '@test.jpg'

 ```

Make sure the request is inheriting Auth from the parent to use your access token

request.description:
**Feature extraction** is the process of finding the most important features in a data set and transforming them into a format that can be used by a machine learning algorithm.

These models return a two-dimensional **feature matrix** where each row represents a data point and each column represents a feature. The values in the matrix represent the strength of the relationship between the data point and the feature.

See available [Feature Extraction models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=feature-extraction&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [facebook/bart-large](https://huggingface.co/facebook/bart-large) | Text-To-Text Transfer Transformer |

**Fill mask** models are trained to predict the missing words in a sentence. The "blank spots" are defined in the input text using a mask token such as `[MASK]`

Note: Mask tokens vary by model. ex: \[MASK\], etc. Check the docs for each model to learn which mask token to use

See available [Fill Mask models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=fill-mask&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [bert-base-uncased](https://huggingface.co/bert-base-uncased) | Mask token: \[MASK\] |
| [bert-base-multilingual-cased](https://huggingface.co/bert-base-multilingual-cased) | Mask token: \[MASK\] |

response.name: [Fill mask] bert-base-uncased

request.description:
**Question Answering** models can be used to answer questions in natural language about a given source text.

See available [(Text) Question Answering models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=question-answering&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [IProject-10/xlm-roberta-base-finetuned-squad2](https://huggingface.co/IProject-10/xlm-roberta-base-finetuned-squad2) | XLM-RoBERTa is a multilingual version of RoBERTa developed by Facebook AI |
| [deepset/roberta-base-squad2](https://huggingface.co/deepset/roberta-base-squad2) | This is the roberta-base model, fine-tuned using the SQuAD2.0 dataset. It's been trained on question-answer pairs, including unanswerable questions, for the task of Question Answering. |

**Sentence Similarity** models calculate how similar various sentences are to a given source sentence.

| [intfloat/multilingual-e5-large](https://huggingface.co/intfloat/multilingual-e5-large) | Multi-lingual sentence similarity |

request.description:
**Text classification** models classify text into one or more categories.  
  
Available categories vary by model. For example, a model may specialize in sentiment analysis (negative/positive/neutral), source langauge, emotions, etc.

See available [Text Classification models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=text-classification&sort=trending)

### Example models

| **model** | **description** |
| --- | --- |
| [SamLowe/roberta-base-go_emotions](https://huggingface.co/SamLowe/roberta-base-go_emotions) | Detects emotions in text based on go_emotions dataset for multi-label classification. |
| [cardiffnlp/twitter-roberta-base-sentiment-latest](https://huggingface.co/cardiffnlp/twitter-roberta-base-sentiment-latest) | Detects negative/neutral/positive sentiment |
| [papluca/xlm-roberta-base-language-detection](https://huggingface.co/papluca/xlm-roberta-base-language-detection?text=I'm+burnt+out) | Detects langauge of source text |
| [nlptown/bert-base-multilingual-uncased-sentiment](https://huggingface.co/nlptown/bert-base-multilingual-uncased-sentiment) | Estimated 1-5 star product review ratings based on source text, multi-lingual |

**Text-to-text** models generate text from text. Generally speaking this can include translation, question answering, summarization, etc., but the example models in this request focus on **text completion.**

See available [Text-to-Text models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=text2text-generation&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [google/flan-t5-xxl](https://huggingface.co/google/flan-t5-xxl) | Text-To-Text Transfer Transformer |
| [juierror/flan-t5-text2sql-with-schema-v2](https://huggingface.co/juierror/flan-t5-text2sql-with-schema-v2) | Specializes in SQL |

response.name: [Text-to-text] juierror/flan-t5-text2sql-with-schema-v2

request.description:
**Token Classification** models can be used to assign a label to each token in a sentence (ex: naming parts of speech, labeling custom categories, identifying key phrases, etc).

See available [Token Classification models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=token-classification&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [tomaarsen/span-marker-mbert-base-multinerd](https://huggingface.co/tomaarsen/span-marker-mbert-base-multinerd) | SpanMarker for Multilingual Named Entity Recognition (15 types: person, vehicle, place, etc...) |
| [tomaarsen/span-marker-bert-base-ncbi-disease](https://huggingface.co/tomaarsen/span-marker-bert-base-ncbi-disease) | SpanMarker for Disease Named Entity Recognition |
| [dslim/bert-base-NER](https://huggingface.co/dslim/bert-base-NER) | Recognize four types of entities: location (LOC), organizations (ORG), person (PER) and Miscellaneous (MISC). |
| [ml6team/keyphrase-extraction-kbir-inspec](https://huggingface.co/ml6team/keyphrase-extraction-kbir-inspec) | Keyphrase extraction |
| [oliverguhr/fullstop-punctuation-multilang-large](https://huggingface.co/oliverguhr/fullstop-punctuation-multilang-large?text=Ho+sentito+che+ti+sei+laureata+il+che+mi+fa+molto+piacere) | Predicts punctuation in text (en, it, fr, de) |

request.description:
**Translation** models specialize in translating text from source to target languages. Some models accept a variety of source languages to translate to a specific target langauge, while other models specialize in certain langauge pairs.

  
See available [](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=summarization&sort=trending)[Translation models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=translation&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [Helsinki-NLP/opus-mt-en-zh](https://huggingface.co/Helsinki-NLP/opus-mt-en-zh) | English > Chinese |
| [Helsinki-NLP/opus-mt-es-en](https://huggingface.co/Helsinki-NLP/opus-mt-es-en?text=Me+llamo+Wolfgang+y+vivo+en+Berlin) | Spanish > English |

**Zero Shot (Text) Classification** is a type of text classification model that can be used to classify text into categories that were not seen during training. You can define which categories for the model to look out for.

See available [Zero Shot (Text) Classification models](https://huggingface.co/models?pipeline_tag=zero-shot-classification&sort=trending)

### Example models

| model | description |
| --- | --- |
| [MoritzLaurer/DeBERTa-v3-base-mnli-fever-anli](https://huggingface.co/MoritzLaurer/DeBERTa-v3-base-mnli-fever-anli) | Base model is DeBERTa-v3-base from Microsoft |
| [facebook/bart-large-mnli](https://huggingface.co/facebook/bart-large-mnli) | NLI-based Zero Shot Text Classification |

response.name: [Zero Shot Classification] MoritzLaurer/DeBERTa-v3-base-mnli-fever-anli
